Creating a drag-and-drop Kanban board in React can be achieved using the following steps:

**Step 1: Set up the project structure**

Create a new React project using `create-react-app` or your preferred method. Create a new directory for your project and navigate into it.

**Step 2: Install required libraries**

Install the required libraries:

```bash
npm install react-draggable
npm install react-beautiful-dnd
```

**Step 3: Create the drag-and-drop component**

Create a new file `DraggableBoard.js` in your project directory:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from'react';
import { Draggable } from'react-draggable';

const DraggableBoard = ({ board, drag, drop, dragStart, dragEnd }) => {
  const [dragging, setDragging] = useState(false);

  const handleDragStart = (event, data) => {
    setDragging(true);
    dragStart(event, data);
  };

  const handleDragEnd = (event, data) => {
    setDragging(false);
    dragEnd(event, data);
  };

  return (
    <div
      ref={drag}
      draggable={dragging}
      onDragStart={handleDragStart}
      onDragEnd={handleDragEnd}
      onDrop={drop}
    >
      {board.map((item, index) => (
        <Draggable key={index} index={index} item={item}>
          {(provided, snapshot) => (
            <div
              ref={provided.innerRef}
              {...snapshot}
              style={{
                height: '100px',
                width: '100px',
                backgroundColor: 'lightblue',
                padding: '10px',
                margin: '10px',
              }}
            >
              {item.name}
            </div>
          )}
        </Draggable>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};

export default DraggableBoard;
```

**Step 4: Create the board container**

Create a new file `BoardContainer.js` in your project directory:

```jsx
import React from'react';
import DraggableBoard from './DraggableBoard';

const BoardContainer = ({ board }) => {
  return (
    <div>
      {board.map((item, index) => (
        <DraggableBoard
          key={index}
          board={item}
          drag={true}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};

export default BoardContainer;
```

**Step 5: Create the app**

Create a new file `App.js` in your project directory:

```jsx
import React from'react';
import BoardContainer from './BoardContainer';

const App = () => {
  const [board, setBoard] = useState([
    { id: 1, name: 'Task 1' },
    { id: 2, name: 'Task 2' },
    { id: 3, name: 'Task 3' },
  ]);

  const handleAddTask = (newTask) => {
    setBoard([...board, newTask]);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <BoardContainer board={board} />
      <button onClick={() => handleAddTask({ id: 4, name: 'Task 4' })}>
        Add Task
      </button>
    </div>
  );
};

export default App;
```

**Step 6: Style the board**

Add some basic styling to your board container:

```jsx
