To add a camera button to your React Native iOS app, you'll need to use the following steps:

1. Create a new React Native project using `npx react-native init CameraApp`.
2. Install the necessary libraries for camera functionality using `npm install react-native-camera`.

Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates how to add a camera button to your app:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from'react';
import { View, Button, TouchableOpacity, Image, Text } from'react-native';
import { Camera } from'react-native-camera';

const App = () => {
  const [camera, setCamera] = useState(null);

  const handlePress = () => {
    if (camera) {
      camera.takePictureAsync().then((image) => {
        console.log('Camera picture taken:', image);
        // Save the image to your device or send it to the server
        // For simplicity, we'll just display it here
        setCamera(null);
        alert('Camera picture taken!');
      }).catch((error) => {
        console.error('Error taking camera picture:', error);
        setCamera(null);
        alert('Error taking camera picture!');
      });
    } else {
      setCamera(new Camera());
    }
  };

  return (
    <View>
      <Button title="Open Camera" onPress={handlePress} />
      {camera? (
        <Camera
          style={{ position: 'absolute', top: 20, right: 20 }}
          type={camera.type}
          ref={(ref) => setCamera(ref)}
        />
      ) : null}
      <View>
        <Image
          source={{ uri: 'https://picsum.photos/200/300' }}
          style={{ width: 100, height: 100, borderRadius: 50 }}
        />
      </View>
    </View>
  );
};

export default App;
```

This code creates a basic React Native app with a button that opens the camera when pressed. The `handlePress` function takes the camera object as a parameter and saves the captured image to the device or sends it to the server. The camera button is also displayed below the button.

Note: You'll need to replace the `https://picsum.photos/200/300` URL with your own image source.

